data.title: Musicians Born on June 20
data.meta_description: Famous birthdays in music for the 20th of June. See which composers, musicians, pop stars and rockers were born on June 20.
data.text:
Lazaro Valvasensi, Italian organist and composer, born in Valvasone, Republic of Venice (d. 1661)

Salvatore Rosa, Italian baroque painter, poet, musician and actor, born in Arenella, Kingdom of Naples, Spanish Habsburg (d. 1673)

Nonnosus Madlseder, German composer and Benedictine monk, born in Merano, County of Tyrol, Austria (d. 1797)

Anna Laetitia Barbauld, English poet and writer of hymns (Life! I Know Not What Thou Art), born in Kibworth Harcourt, Leicestershire, England (d. 1825)

Joseph Martin Kraus, German-Swedish composer, known as "the Swedish Mozart", conductor, and pedagogue, born in Miltenberg am Main, Electorate of Bavaria, Holy Roman Empire (d. 1792)

Jacques Offenbach, German-French composer (Tales of Hoffmann), born in Cologne, Kingdom of Prussia (d. 1880)

Arthur Battelle Whiting, American composer and teacher, born in Cambridge, Massachusetts (d. 1936)

Giannotto Bastianelli, Italian musician and composer, born in Fiesole, Kingdom of Italy (d. 1927)

Wilfred Pelletier, Canadian conductor (Voice of Firestone), born in Montreal, Quebec (d. 1982)

Elisabeth Hauptmann, German writer (co-author of The Threepenny Opera), born in Peckelsheim, Westphalia, German Empire (d. 1973)

Anthon van der Horst, Dutch organist and composer, born in Amsterdam, Netherlands (d. 1965)

Bob Howard, American singer and pianist (Sing it Again), born in Newton, Massachusetts (d. 1986)

Jimmy Driftwood, American folk songwriter and musician, born in Mountain View, Arkansas (d. 1998)

Friedrich Zipp, German composer, born in Frankfurt, Germany (d. 1997)

(Donato) "Danny" Cedrone, American guitarist and bandleader (The Esquires; Bill Haley & His Comets - "Rock Around The Clock"), born in Jamesville, New York (d. 1954)

Chet Atkins, American guitarist (Me & My Guitar), born in Luttrell, Tennessee (d. 2001)

John M Dengler, American jazz multi-instrumentalist - bass sax/trumpet/trombone (The Intensely Vigorous Jazz Band), born in East Stroudsburg, Pennsylvania (d. 1994) [1]

Eric Dolphy, American jazz saxophone, bass clarinet, and flute player, born in Los Angeles, California (d. 1964)

Ingrid Haebler, Austrian pianist (Haydn/Mozart/Schubert), born in Vienna, Austria (d. 2023) [1]

Arne Nordheim, Norwegian conductor and composer (Aftonland; Canzona per orchestra; Poly-poly), born in Larvik, Norway (d. 2010)

Danny Aiello, American stage and screen actor (Moonstruck; Do the Right Thing; Broadway Danny Rose), and singer, born in New York City (d. 2019)

Alain Bancquart, French violist, contemporary classical composer, and musical director, born in Dieppe, France (d. 2022)

1934 Cornel Țăranu, Romanian composer (Garlands), born in Cluj, Romania (d. 2023)

Billy Guy [Frank Phillips], American baritone pop singer (The Coasters, 1955-73 - "Charlie Brown"; "Youngblood"), and record producer, born in Itasca, Texas (d. 2002)

Jerry Keller, American pop singer-songwriter ("Here Comes Summer"), and actor (If Ever I See You Again), born in Fort Smith, Arkansas

Mickie Most [Michael Hayes], British record producer (Herman's Hermits, The Nashville Teens, Donovan, Lulu), born in Aldershot, Hampshire, England (d. 2003)

1938 Nikolai Martynov, Soviet Russian composer and musicologist, born in Leningrad, Russia, USSR

Brian Wilson

American singer-songwriter, vocal arranger, and producer (Beach Boys - "In My Room"; "Good Vibrations"; "God Only Knows"; Caroline No"), born in Inglewood, California

(Morna) Anne Murray, Canadian pop singer ("Snow Bird"; "You Needed Me"), born in Springhill, Nova Scotia

André Watts, American-Hungarian concert pianist, and educator, born in Nuremberg, Germany (d. 2023) [1]

Dolores Brooks, American singer (The Crystals - "Then He Kissed Me"; "Da Doo Ron Ron"), born in Brooklyn, New York

Alan Longmuir, Scottish pop-rock musician (Bay City Rollers - "Saturday Night"), born in Edinburgh, Scotland (d. 2018)

1948 Nigel Morris, British Jazz-fusion drummer (Isotope), born in London, England

Bob Andrews, English rock keyboardist and producer (Brinsley Schwarz; The Rumour), born in Leeds, Yorkshire, England

Lionel Richie

American singer (Commodores, 1968-82; "Easy"; "Three Times A Lady"; solo -"Hello"; "All Night Long"), and TV personality (American Idol, 2018-22), born in Tuskegee, Alabama

Peter Gordon, American composer (Love of Life Orchestra), born in New York City

Michael Anthony [Sobolewski], American rock bassist/singer (Van Halen - "Pretty Woman"), born in Chicago, Illinois

(Beranadette) "Kelly" Johnson, British heavy metal guitarist (Girlschool - "St. Valentine's Day Massacre"), born in Edmonton, London, England (d. 2007)

John Taylor, English musician (Duran Duran), born in Solihull, Warwickshire

Eddy Shaver, American country-rock guitarist and songwriter, born in Waco, Texas (d. 2000)

Amir Derakh [Davidson], American rock guitarist, and synthesizer player (Orgy; Julien-K), born in Schenectady, New York

Francis Reyes, Filipino new wave and Pinoy rock guitarist (The Dawn), broadcaster, and music editor, born in Lipa City, Batangas, Philippines

1967 Joey Cathcart, American rock guitarist (Nelson - "Love & Affection"), born in Los Angeles, California (d. 2021)

1967 [Matthew] Murphy Karges, American bassist (Sugar Ray - "Every Morning"), born in Orange County, California

Jeordie White, American rock bassist (Marilyn Manson), born in Pompton Lakes, New Jersey

Chino Moreno, American heavy metal vocalist and lyricist (Deftones), born in Sacramento, California

Jerome Fontamillas, Filipino-American rock keyboardist (Switchfoot), born in Pasay, Philippines

Charlotte Hatherley, English rock guitarist (Ash, 1997-2006), and composer, born in London, England

Tony Lovato, American singer and guitarist (Mest), born in Blue Island, Illinois

Caroline Polachek, American pop singer-songwriter (Chairlift - "Bruises"; solo - "So Hot You're Hurting My Feelings"), born in Manhattan, New York

Nia Sioux, American dancer and singer (Dance Moms), born in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania
